
Overview of noun hawker

The noun hawker has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (1) peddler, pedlar, packman, hawker, pitchman -- (someone who travels about selling his wares (as on the streets or at carnivals))
2. falconer, hawker -- (a person who breeds and trains hawks and who follows the sport of falconry)
